				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\mathrm {BaTiO}_3$$\end{document} beam can sustain almost five times the inhomogeneous strain compared to a corresponding macro beam. Deng et al. [32] showed that decreasing the thickness of a flexoelectric beam made of polyvinylidene fluoride (PVDF) from 3 μ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
