Many previous works have pointed out the dominance of the flexoelectric effect over the piezoelectric effect at the micro-scale [32, 35]. To accurately capture the flexodynamic effect at lower scale, the eigenfrequencies should be evaluated properly. The variation of the first eigenfrequency of the cantilever beam from Fig. 3 with respect to sample thickness is investigated. The material parameters of SrTiO3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
